A '''heraldic kiteshield''' is a decorative [[Steel kiteshield|steel]], [[Adamant kiteshield|adamant]] or [[rune kiteshield]]. Players can paint them on a [[shield easel]] or [[banner easel]] in a [[player-owned house]] if they have level 43 [[Crafting]] or higher and have been assigned a crest by [[Sir Renitee]] in the [[White Knights' Castle]]. Sir Renitee will not assign a crest unless the player has over level 16 [[Construction]]. A player's first crest assignment is free, and it costs 5,000 coins to change your crest to another one, however some crests have other requirements, detailed below. Players can use a shield easel in another players house if they do not have one in theirs. The shields have exactly the same stats as their steel, adamant or rune counterparts.

If a player is killed by [[Player killing|another player]], the shield will convert into a steel/adamant/rune kiteshield if it is not protected upon death, depending on the shield the player used to make the heraldic kiteshield.

'''Note:''' As of an [[Update:QoL_and_Treasure_Trails_Feedback_Changes|update]], the Saradomin and Zamorak heraldic shields '''will''' offer protection in the [[God Wars Dungeon]].

